Amaury JACQUOT wrote:
> Btw :
> Is there a way to use ACls under Linux ?
> This is a requirement for C2 (and above) clasification.
> it would be fun to have C2 classification for linux...
ACLs are not required until B3. Audit is required at C2, and
audit is a feature that requires careful consideration as
some implementations have proven to be resource intensive.
